  "prompt": "Can I use an unverified Paypal account to receive payments?",
  "response": "Yes, you can use an unverified PayPal account to receive payments, but there are certain limitations and restrictions you may face. Unverified accounts often come with lower transaction limits, and using one may raise security concerns for your customers, which could affect their trust in your business. Additionally, PayPal may impose restrictions on your account until it is verified, such as holding funds or limiting access to certain features.\n\nTo verify your PayPal account, you typically need to link and confirm a bank account or credit card, and sometimes provide additional identification information.\n\nVerifying your account can help ensure smoother transactions, increased trust from customers, raised transaction limits, and more secure payment processing.",
